{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17500774","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17500774"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:17:29+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:17:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1669"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1669","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1669"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.36,0.25,0.22,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1669"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106192"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1669","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1669"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1669"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88665"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"433"},{"type":"tags","id":"2076"},{"type":"tags","id":"4963"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"8791"},{"type":"tags","id":"9022"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11636"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12912"},{"type":"tags","id":"12922"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1793"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1875"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6816"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7223"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36305"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36306"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38737"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39097"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43090"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43984"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106192","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/106192"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 80-year-old man presents with a four month history of significant deterioration of vision. He has a past ocular history of cataract surgery and dry age-related macular degeneration for which he takes Macu-Vision tablets. 15 years ago he was started on glibenclamide for type 2 diabetes and he takes perindopril for hypertension. He has a 30 pack-year smoking history and has a BMI of 35. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHis visual acuity in the right eye is 6/9 and the left eye is 6/60. His anterior segment examination is unremarkable. Fundoscopy is performed - this image displays his left eye posterior pole. The rest of the physical examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely explanation for his visual change?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Central retinal artery occlusion","Age-related macular degeneration","Diabetes mellitus","Hypertension","Nutritional optic neuropathy"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA subacute history of vision loss, along with an elevated macula with surrounding multi-layer retinal haemorrhages is consistent with a bleeding choroidal neovascular membrane secondary to wet \u003Cstrong\u003Eage related macular degeneration \u003C/strong\u003E(ARMD). There are drusen (yellow/white spots) below the macula suggestive of dry ARMD. There are two types of ARMD: about 90% are \u0022dry\u0022 with drusen, gradual progressive atrophy and pigment aggregation bordering areas of depigmentation. There is no proven therapy to reverse progression however to stop progression of mild to moderate dry ARMD there is evidence suggesting to stop smoking and to initiate Macu-Vision vitamin tablets. The other 10% are \u0022wet\u0022 ARMD with formation of an choroidal neovascular membrane which can exudate or bleed requiring treatment with intravitreal Anti-Vascular Endothelial Growth Factor.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECentral retinal artery occlusion\u003C/strong\u003E presents with a sudden, painless vision loss and a pale retina with a \u0027cherry red\u0027 spot. \u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetic\u003C/strong\u003E eye disease will show a fundus with micro-aneurysms, cotton wool spots, and hard exudates. Haemorrhages will be usually be smaller flame or dot-blot haemorrhages. \u003Cstrong\u003EHypertensive\u003C/strong\u003E eye disease will show signs of arteriolar narrowing, arteriovenous nipping, copper wiring, and in later stages dot-blot or flame haemorrhages. \u003Cstrong\u003ENutritional optic neuropathy \u003C/strong\u003Ecan occur secondary to severe chronic alcohol intake and smoking.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Age-related macular degeneration is a common and important cause of visual loss in older patients.","Smoking is a significant risk factor for progression of age-related macular degeneration"],"references":["Apte RA. Age-Related Macular Degeneration. N Engl J Med 2021; 385:539-47. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34347954/","Fleckenstein M, Keenan TDL, Guymer RH, Chakravarthy U, Schmitz-Valckenberg S, Klaver CC, Wong WT, Chew EY. Age-related macular degeneration. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2021 May 6;7(1):31. doi: 10.1038/s41572-021-00265-2. PMID: 33958600. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33958600/","Khachigian LM, Liew G, Teo KYC, Wong TY, Mitchell P. Emerging therapeutic strategies for unmet need in neovascular age-related macular degeneration. J Transl Med. 2023 Feb 21;21(1):133. doi: 10.1186/s12967-023-03937-7. PMID: 36810060; PMCID: PMC9942398. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9942398/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88665"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1669"}},"stemMe